President Muhammadu Buhari is expected to visit Gombe State Monday to commission projects executed by Governor Ibrahim Hassan Dankwambo. Security has been beefed up across the metropolis ahead of the president visit, where he would commission some of the Dankwambo’s ‘Landmark Projects.’ Our correspondent who went around the state capital reported that security agents have been placed at strategic locations where the president is expected to visit and commission the projects. Some of the projects expected to be commissioned are the International Conference Centre, Gombe City Gate and Tanker Parking Bay, along Bauchi road, Women and Children Hospital and several township roads. Others are College of Medical Sciences of the Gombe State University and Remodelled Hassan Central Primary School, among others. It was learnt that Buhari would arrive the Gombe International Airport by 12:00 noon. The state Commissioner of Information and Orientation, Alhaji Umar Ahmed Nafada enjoined all residents of the state to come out en-masse to welcome the president. ‘Dankwambo, not Goje, is PDP leader in Gombe’ Day Gombe stood still for Buhari Gombe: The battle between Dankwambo and Yahaya Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin